# Warning and error alerts (Mantine)

For **warnings** (`color="yellow"`, `color="orange"`, `color="amber"`) and **errors** (`color="red"`):

- Use the default **filled** Alert (omit `variant`, or set `variant="filled"`).
- Do **not** use `variant="light"` for warnings – it looks muddy in dark mode and is too weak.

Neutral/info alerts (`gray`, `blue`) may use `variant="light"` when a subtle tone is intended.

```tsx
// Good
<Alert color="yellow" title="Encryption not configured">...</Alert>

// Avoid for warnings
<Alert color="yellow" variant="light" title="...">...</Alert>
```
